  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Haiti Hope MicroCredit</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Entrepreneurs</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Some of the activities are: 1) Customer reviews of business plans or activities, coach, and provide additional business training; 2) Promote the exchange between clients through coaching by loan officers; 3) Analyze the demand for loans; 4) Visit and evaluate the activities of customers; 5) Loan disbursement; 6) Support customers after the disbursement of loans; and 7) Ensure periodic reimbursement of loans disbursed.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Haiti Hope Microcredit project aims to improve living conditions of 4,000 underserved women and men peasants, traders, and entrepreneurs in Haiti through economic and social development. The project offers financial and business support through loan disbursement; training in entrepreneurship, management, and operations; and the facilitation exchange groups to encourage networking, partnership, exchange of ideas, and the adoption of best practices.</narrative>
  </description>
